description:
This is a 15 minute workout called 'Physio Guided Lower Back Stretches for Beginners (15 Minute Routine)' from the channel Michelle Kenway.
The workout falls under Flexibility/Stretching.
It's suitable for Beginner fitness levels.
The workout has a The Reboot Workout and The Zen Flow vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: These gentle lower back stretches reduce back stiffness and improve spinal flexibility. This Physiotherapist guided stretching routine includes stretches for the muscles and joints of the lower back along with hamstring, buttock and hip flexor muscles to also help prevent lower back pain. These safe stretching exercises are suitable for beginners- intermediate general flexibility training rather that treatment for a specific lower back condition.

#lowerbackstretches #exercisesforbeginners #WithMe 

Website: https://www.pelvicexercises.com.au

These lower back exercises include static stretches and mobility exercises for improving lower back flexibility. These stretches are performed lying down on a firm surface. This beginners stretching routine commences with lumbar rotations and pelvic tilts for mobility warm up.
